column1: #Text=The latest maintenance of MDO has been migrated to \[LiUSemWeb/Materials-Design-Ontology\](https://github.com/LiUSemWeb/Materials-Design-Ontology).   ### What is Materials Design Ontology?

#Text=MDO is an ontology for materials design field, representing the domain knowledge specifically related to solid-state physics and computational materials science.  ### What does Materials Design Ontology consist of?

#Text=Materials Design Ontology consists of 4 modules which are:  \* \[Core\](https://w3id.org/mdo/core/1.0): This module consists of the top-level concepts and relationships of the materials design ontology, which are also reused in other modules
#Text=\* \[Structure\](https://w3id.org/mdo/structure/1.0): The structure module is intended to represent the structural information of materials.
#Text=Such structural information is also the basis of materials calculations
#Text=\* \[Calculation\](https://w3id.org/mdo/calculation/1.0): This module is intended to represent the classification of different computational methods
#Text=\* \[Provenance\](https://w3id.org/mdo/provenance/1.0): This module is intended to represent the provenance information of materials data and calculation
#Text=\* A full MDO importing all the above modules is avaliable at \[MDO Full\](https://w3id.org/mdo/full/1.0).  ### MDO Concepts and Relationships !
